# .funcignore — Azure Functions Core Tools packaging exclusion manifest
#
# IMPORTANT: node_modules/ is intentionally NOT listed here.
# Azure/static-web-apps-deploy@v1 excludes node_modules/ from the API zip by
# default (platform-level packager behavior, independent of .gitignore).
# The postbuild script (scripts/materialize-api-externals.mjs) copies the
# externalized OTel + AppInsights packages from repo-root node_modules into
# packages/web/api/node_modules/ so they ship in the SWA deployment zip.
# Listing node_modules/ here would re-exclude those materialized packages,
# breaking all API endpoints at runtime (MODULE_NOT_FOUND → 0 routes → 404).
# See: https://github.com/azure-management-and-platforms/kickstart/issues/1041
#
# Upstream reference: Azure/azure-functions-core-tools
#   src/Cli/func/StaticResources/funcignore (SHA 17bd0f697c2d413e7ca64b117dd1456a8fdda716)

# Source maps — bloat the upload zip, not needed at runtime
*.js.map

# TypeScript source — compiled to dist/, raw .ts files serve no purpose in deploy
*.ts

# Git internals
.git*

# Editor / local config
.vscode

# Local development settings — must never ship (contains secrets)
local.settings.json
local.settings.json.template

# Docs
getting_started.md
CHANGELOG.md
OBSERVABILITY.md

# Test fixtures
test

# TypeScript compiler artifacts
*.tsbuildinfo

# Build config and source — not needed at runtime (P2, per Zapp review)
src/
scripts/
esbuild.config.mjs
tsconfig.json

# Node type definitions and dev-only packages — not needed at runtime
node_modules/@types/
node_modules/azure-functions-core-tools/
node_modules/typescript/
node_modules/esbuild/
node_modules/vite/
